Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-red; cream slip. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Xenophanes. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0188.23. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0870)
